  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Higher model risk drives stricter credibility requirements; Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed. All project requirements have been reviewed against the 13-factor credibility framework; seven factors have been assessed and six remain flagged as epistemic gaps consistent with MRL 5. This package is submitted under the Minimal profile; structured bindsRequirement linkage is deferred to full-profile submission.",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/cou2-vad-hemolysis-claim",
